    "reasoning": "Now I have the figures I need. Let me calculate:\n\nQ1 2026:\n- Consolidated Revenue: $4,694 million\n- Connectivity Revenue: $3,257 million\n\nFY2025:\n- Consolidated Revenue: $18,674 million\n- Connectivity Revenue: $11,387 million\n\nAnnualized Q1 2026:\n- Consolidated: $4,694 \u00d7 4 = $18,776 million\n- Connectivity: $3,257 \u00d7 4 = $13,028 million\n\nGrowth rates (annualized Q1 2026 vs FY2025):\n- Consolidated: ($18,776 - $18,674) / $18,674 = $102 / $18,674 = 0.546% \u2248 0.55%\n- Connectivity: ($13,028 - $11,387) / $11,387 = $1,641 / $11,387 = 14.41%\n\nLet me also calculate the implied growth for the other segments to understand the concentration:\n\nQ1 2026 segments:\n- Space: $619M\n- Connectivity: $3,257M\n- AI: $818M\n- Total: $4,694M\n\nFY2025 segments:\n- Space: $4,086M\n- Connectivity: $11,387M\n- AI: $3,201M\n- Total: $18,674M\n\nAnnualized Q1 2026:\n- Space: $619 \u00d7 4 = $2,476M\n- Connectivity: $3,257 \u00d7 4 = $13,028M\n- AI: $818 \u00d7 4 = $3,272M\n- Total: $18,776M\n\nGrowth rates:\n- Space: ($2,476 - $4,086) / $4,086 = -$1,610 / $4,086 = -39.40% (decline)\n- Connectivity: ($13,028 - $11,387) / $11,387 = $1,641 / $11,387 = 14.41%\n- AI: ($3,272 - $3,201) / $3,201 = $71 / $3,201 = 2.22%\n- Consolidated: ($18,776 - $18,674) / $18,674 = $102 / $18,674 = 0.55%\n\nSo the consolidated growth is essentially flat (0.55%), but Connectivity is growing at 14.41%. This suggests that the consolidated momentum is heavily concentrated in the Connectivity segment, while Space is declining significantly and AI is roughly flat.\n\nLet me verify these calculations with the calculator tool.",
